# Keep GitHub's downloadable archives limited to the plugin's runtime files.
#
# `git archive` powers both the release "Source code" assets and the repo's
# "Code -> Download ZIP" button. Anything marked `export-ignore` is dropped from
# that output, so a user who downloads the repo as a zip and installs it gets a
# clean plugin — not the CI config, dev docs, or git metadata that would ride
# along otherwise. (The release workflow builds its own named asset from an
# explicit file list, so this is a second, independent layer of the same intent.)
/.github        export-ignore
/.gitignore     export-ignore
/.gitattributes export-ignore
/README.md      export-ignore
/CHANGELOG.md   export-ignore
